history.content:
I've taken 161, 188, 170, and I'm currently in EE 126. For me at least, 126 is way harder than 170, and 170 is slightly more difficult and far more time consuming than the other two classes. 

Personally, I would not take 170 and 126 at the same time. To give you an idea of where I'm coming from, I got straight A- in the relevant pre-reqs for these classes (EE16 A/B, CS 70, CS 61B). Only if you easily got As in those classes would I take them at the same time.

children.subject: (not OP) Do you think 16B and 126 would be doable together?
If you're comfortable with 16A material, then that should be manageable. I'd pair lighter courses like CS 161/168/188 with EE 126 though if I were you.

Do EE 126 in a semester where that is your only tech, or only if you're taking it with a really light technical. I tried 126 + 127 (my only two technical courses for the semester) at the same time and it is not fun, and I can normally handle 3 EECS upper divs per semester really easily. 170 is comparable in difficulty to 127, so I would definitely not recommend.

history.content:
Has anyone experienced a semester taking EE126 + CS170? How would you describe it?

I was planning to do this next semester, but I also need to take another CS upper division course. What would you recommend besides CS188, which I am taking now? I was thinking maybe CS161...

Thanks for your insights!
